author: Cleo Abram
description:
This is rare footage of an apex predator from 1933... it’s called the Tasmanian Tiger, and its one of the very last of its kind!

They went extinct in 1982. But now… scientists are trying to bring them BACK.

Scientists are working to sequence Tasmanian Tiger DNA and edit their closest living relative, and make an animal that COULD take back its place in the ecosystem… 

If you want to see how it’s going, subscribe!

#shorts #thylacine #DNA #tasmaniantiger  #predator #science
title: This Apex Predator Went Extinct. They're Bringing It Back.
